Rating: 4
Really good dessert and easy to make. I did not make the sauce as directed but instead used frozen mixed fruits and add a little sugar to them along with lemon zest and juice from one lemon. Warmed up the sauce and then let it cool. I had it in a pretty bowl to serve along with the dessert but forgot to put it out. Oh well. It is now in the freezer for a later date. Obviously, the dessert was yummy without any sauce. Enjoy making it.

Rating: 4
This is a wonderful recipe that can be easily adjusted- 5 years ago I brought this to a Passover seder and my hosts have insisted I bring it every year since. I have tried melting chocolate chips on the crust, using raspberry jam, vanilla ice cream and raspberry sauce. It too was excellent. One friend routinely makes this for 4th of July adding a blueberry garnish to achieve "red,white and blue".

